From:MCsweet
Analysts vs stock efficiency,

I agree with Madharry that I think there is more opportunity/inefficiency in
stocks covered by fewer analysts (or not covered at all). In the later case,
you may be one of the few people have done homework on the stock. Every once in
awhile, I am in a situation where I think I know about as much about the
company as anyone else who is not in the company or a related party. That
doesn't mean I always get it right, but my odds are usually better (IMO).

That being said, it doesn't make it impossible for the analysts to get it wrong
or that there are no opportunities in stocks covered by analysts. In the case
of ATPG, it appears to be a high risk/high reward stock, so it could generate a
high return despite analyst coverage because it is perceived as a high risk
stock.

MC
