From:Paul Senior
Cwillyg, I don't know about your specific company (p/bk of 2, p/e 7-8), but
looking through my insurance company positions, I've got a goodly number that
trade below 1.2x stated bv and under 8x, where the company also seems to have
profits each year, stable - if not growing. Just catching my eye, here are SUR,
TRH, ACE, AFG, ESGR. My preference of course has been to buy a package of these
companies.

Regarding financial accounting, here's something I ran across from ANAT's
annual report, something that surprised me:

"American National recorded $98.9 Million of other than temporary impairments
during 2009, primarily due to stock valuations in the first quarter. However,
many of the securities impaired in 2008 and early 2009 rebounded to show
unrealized gains at the end of 2009. Due to accounting rules, these gains are
not allowed to be reflected in income until the instruments are disposed of."
