Date:4/21/2010 3:52:02 PM
From:Dr. Ipsofacto
I'm not sure it's "mimicking" irrational behavior as much as taking a time-out
until the market comes to its senses. If a value stock shows strong irrational
downward momentum, I think it's perfectly rational for a value investor to get
out.

If I'm in a nice bar when a brawl breaks out, I don't mind stepping outside
until the brawl is over. There's no sense in risking a Shiner Bock to the head.
Hell, there might even be another nice bar across the street with cheaper
Shiner - and no brawl.

I think the key here is strong irrational downward momentum. I completely agree
value investors shouldn't chase momentum. I certainly don't make it a practice.
However, I don't think we should ignore it completely.

Regards,
Dr.I
